  "text": "In Spain, between the year 2006 (no crisis period) and the year 2012 (crisis period), economic and social situations have been modified; the government significantly cut the public health budget during the crisis period, and those budgets cuts had implications in food access and quality [CITATION_1] . The Spanish federation of food bank reported a significant increase in the quantity of food distributed among this period. The number of people demanding this service grew from 700000 to 1.5 million (Antentas and Vivas 2014).",
